SUMMARY:Deadline: Stichting NORMA: NORMA Fonds Project Grant (round 4\, 202
 6)
DESCRIPTION:The NORMA Fonds redistributes copyright remuneration collected 
 by Stichting NORMA into cultural\, social and professional projects involv
 ing performing artists\, and is one of the few Dutch schemes with four int
 akes a year and a genuinely short cycle. Both arts-sector organisations an
 d individual arts professionals may apply\, though the applicant needs a b
 ank account and legal footing and cannot be a BIS-funded institution. The 
 project must centre on performing artists in the copyright sense\, meaning
  people who perform a copyright-protected work: musicians\, dancers\, acto
 rs\, voice actors. This fits live experimental music\, sound performance a
 nd performative media-art work\, but not object-based exhibitions or non-p
 erformative installation programmes. The maximum grant is EUR 10\,000\, th
 e total project budget must stay under EUR 150\,000\, the applicant's annu
 al budget under EUR 500\,000\, and at least a quarter of the project budge
 t must be earned from audience income\, so this is a top-up rather than a 
 primary funding source. Budgets must honour NORMA's 2026 performer wage no
 rms. Applications are submitted online during a one-month window each quar
 ter\; the next round runs 1 to 30 October 2026\, closing at 23:59. TIMING 
 RULE: decisions arrive no later than eight weeks after the deadline\, and 
 the premiere date must fall at least eight weeks after the application dea
 dline. Organisations that already received a NORMA Fonds grant in 2024 or 
 2025 are excluded\, and supporting staff may not exceed 2 FTE.\n\nOrganisa
 tion: Stichting NORMA (collecting society for performing artists)\nLocatio
 n: Netherlands-based arts-sector activity. No city or region restriction s
 tated.\nAward: Maximum EUR 10\,000 per project. Total project budget may n
 ot exceed EUR 150\,000 and the applicant organisation's annual budget may 
 not exceed EUR 500\,000. At least 25 percent of the project budget must co
 me from audience or box-office revenue. Performer fees must meet the 2026 
 wage norms of EUR 139 per rehearsal and EUR 340 per performance. No applic
 ation fee.\nDuration: Single project\, typically a production or concert s
 eries. Final report due within six months of completion.\n\nMore: https://
 www.stichtingnorma.nl/norma-fonds/aanvragen/?utm_source=artificialnouveaug
 rantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://www.stichtingnorma.nl/norma-fonds/aanvragen/?utm_source=artific
 ialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Netherlands-based arts-sector activity. No city or region restrict
 ion stated.
